@startuml
title Project 8 - Full Domain Model Architecture
top to bottom direction
scale max 2400 width
hide empty members
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 180
skinparam nodesep 100
skinparam ranksep 140
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam packageTitleAlignment center
skinparam packageTitleFontStyle bold
skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor #FCFCFC
  BorderColor #4F4F4F
  ArrowColor #4F4F4F
}
skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor<<main>> #D9EAD3
  BorderColor<<main>> #38761D
}
skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor<<shared>> #E8D5F5
  BorderColor<<shared>> #7B2D8B
}
skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor<<level0>> #FFE6E6
  BorderColor<<level0>> #CC0000
}
skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor<<level1>> #FFE6B3
  BorderColor<<level1>> #FF9900
}
skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor<<level2>> #FFFFCC
  BorderColor<<level2>> #CCCC00
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF8DC
  BorderColor #B7A56A
}

note as RelationshipCorrections
  <b>Relationship cardinalities corrected by LLM review</b>
  ChangeEvent --> QueueItem → ChangeEvent "1" -- "0..*" QueueItem
    Reason: PlantUML "-->" is a directed association but lacks cardinality; the corrected relationship indicates a queue item may have zero or more change events, not the other way around.
  Patient "1" --o "1" UserAuthenticationSystem → Patient "1" -- "1" UserAuthenticationSystem
    Reason: A one-to-many aggregation from Patient to UserAuthenticationSystem is incorrect; a patient uses a single authentication system, so a simple one-to-one association is appropriate.
  PatientDatabase ..> SymptomRecord → PatientDatabase "1" o-- "0..*" SymptomRecord
    Reason: A dependency suggests a weaker relationship but the domain requires the database to own symptom records; corrected to an aggregation from database to records.
  Queue *-- QueueItem → Queue "1" --* "0..*" QueueItem
    Reason: The arrow "*--" indicates many on left, but Queue should own many QueueItems; reversal corrects to composition where Queue has many items.
  Queue *-- "ordered list" Patient → Queue "1" --* "0..*" QueueItem
    Reason: A queue contains queue items (not patients directly) and the ordered list constraint is better modeled as a composition with an ordering annotation; correcting the right class to QueueItem.
  REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 "1" -- "1" Actor → REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 "1" -- "1" UrgencyLevel
    Reason: REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 likely represents a requirement or use case, not directly associated with Actor, Permission, or State; it should only relate to UrgencyLevel as a requirement specification.
  REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 "1" -- "1" Permission → REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 "1" -- "1" UrgencyLevel
    Reason: Same as above; all other associations for REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 except to UrgencyLevel are inappropriate for this domain.
  REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 "1" -- "1" State → REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 "1" -- "1" UrgencyLevel
    Reason: Same as above; only the association with UrgencyLevel is relevant.
  REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 "1" -- "many" Interface → REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 "1" -- "1" UrgencyLevel
    Reason: Same as above; only UrgencyLevel association is intended.
  REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 "1" -- "many" Resource → REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 "1" -- "1" UrgencyLevel
    Reason: Same as above; only UrgencyLevel association is intended.
  Resource "1" -- "1" Actor → Resource "1" -- "0..*" Actor
    Reason: A resource is associated with zero or more actors (users), not necessarily exactly one; the cardinality should reflect optionality.
  Resource "1" -- "many" Actor → Resource "1" -- "0..*" Actor
    Reason: Same as above; the multiplicity on the right should be 0..* rather than 'many' which is ambiguous.
  Resource "1" o-- "0..1" UrgencyLevel → Resource "1" -- "1" UrgencyLevel
    Reason: A resource should have exactly one urgency level, not an optional 0..1; the task requires each item to have an urgency.
  Symptom "1" -- "0..1" SymptomRecord → Symptom "1" -- "1" SymptomRecord
    Reason: A symptom is a single occurrence and corresponds to exactly one symptom record; the original optionality suggests a symptom may not have a record, which contradicts the registration requirement.
  SymptomRecord "0..1" --o "1" PatientDatabase → SymptomRecord "0..*" --o "1" PatientDatabase
    Reason: The aggregation direction and cardinality are reversed; a symptom record is aggregated into at most one patient database, but a database can contain many records.
end note

note as ArchitectureCorrections
  <b>Architecture mistakes corrected automatically</b>
  [missing_relationship] There is no relationship between Patient and SymptomRecord, yet Task #53 requires recording symptom information.
    Fix applied: add_relation
  [missing_relationship] There is no relationship between Queue and Patient, yet Tasks #55, #56, #57 involve a queue of patients.
    Fix applied: add_relation
  [missing_relationship] There is no relationship between ChangeEvent and Queue, but Task #56 requires queue reordering on change.
    Fix applied: add_relation
end note

package "Task #53\nRegister patient with\nsymptoms" {
  class Patient <<main>> <<level0>>
  interface PatientDatabase
  class Symptom
  class SymptomRecord
  class UserAuthenticationSystem
}

package "Task #54\nAssign urgency level\n(1-5)" {
  enum UrgencyLevel <<main>> <<level1>>
  class Actor
  class Interface
  enum Permission
  class REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01
  class Resource
  class State
}

package "Task #55\nOrder queue by urgency\nthen time" {
  class Queue <<main>> <<level2>>
  class QueueItem
}

package "Task #56\nReorder queue on change" {
  note as TaskSummary56
    No new domain model classes
    Uses: Queue, Patient, UrgencyLevel
  end note
}

package "Task #57\nTake next patient from\nhead" {
  note as TaskSummary57
    No new domain model classes
    Uses: Patient, Queue
  end note
}

package "Task #58\nLive dashboard with\nurgency and wait time" {
  note as TaskSummary58
    No new domain model classes
    Uses: Patient, UrgencyLevel, Queue
  end note
}

package "Shared / Cross-Task Classes\n[not owned by a single task]" <<Rectangle>> {
  class ChangeEvent <<shared>>
  note right of ChangeEvent : "appears only in relations; not owned by any task"
  interface QueueManagementSystem <<shared>>
  note right of QueueManagementSystem : "appears only in relations; not owned by any task"
}

ChangeEvent "1" -- "0..*" QueueItem
Patient "1" -- "0..*" Symptom
Patient "1" -- "1" UserAuthenticationSystem
PatientDatabase "1" o-- "0..*" SymptomRecord
Queue "1" --* "0..*" QueueItem
QueueItem "1" --> "1" UrgencyLevel
QueueManagementSystem --> Queue
REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 "1" -- "1" UrgencyLevel
Resource "1" -- "0..*" Actor
Resource "1" -- "1" UrgencyLevel
Symptom "1" -- "1" SymptomRecord
SymptomRecord "0..*" --o "1" PatientDatabase
note right of UrgencyLevel #FDFDE0
  <b>SUGGESTION #1 (not applied)</b>
  [introduce_value_object] Consider making\nUrgencyLevel a value object (e.g., with range\n1-5 and validation) instead of an enum, to\nbetter encapsulate its behavior and constraints.
end note

note right of REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01 #FDFDE0
  <b>SUGGESTION #2 (not applied)</b>
  [rename_for_clarity] Rename\n'REQ_ITEM_URGENCY_01' to a descriptive name like\n'ItemUrgency' to align with ubiquitous language\nand improve clarity.
end note

@enduml